    "As explained above, we can use Wilcoxon signed-rank test to estimate whether the differences between two models are significant with respect to any evaluation metric, but this test is not ideal when comparing several models.",
    "Namely, while we can repeat Wilcoxon tests between each pair of models, the risk of type I error increases with multiple comparisons.",
    "Adjusting the level of significance by Bonferroni correction has been suggested as a solution 44 but it is overly radical 4.",
    "Instead, the better approach in a situation where we have K models evaluated in J data sets is to perform Friedman's test 4.",
